@model WalkingTec.Mvvm.Doc.ViewModels.MajorVms.MajorVm

<wt:fieldset field-set-style="Simple" title="UEditor">
  <p>Common properties of rich text box are:</p>
  <table lay-filter="parse-table-demo">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th lay-data="{field:'username', width:200}">properties</th>
        <th lay-data="{field:'joinTime', width:600}">Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Id</td>
        <td>Control ID, generated by default according to the bound field name</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Field</td>
        <td>Binding field,required</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Name</td>
        <td>Control name, generated by default according to the bound field name</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>LabelText</td>
        <td>Label content</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>LabelWidth</td>
        <td>Label length, default= 80</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>HideLabel</td>
        <td>Hide label,or not</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>EmptyText</td>
        <td>Prompt text when there is no data</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Height</td>
        <td>Height of rich text box, default:200px</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Width</td>
        <td>Width of rich text box, default:100%</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <div style="height:10px;">&nbsp;</div>
  <wt:tab>
    <wt:tabheaders>
      <wt:tabheader title="Effect" />
      <wt:tabheader title="Code" />
    </wt:tabheaders>
    <wt:tabcontents>
      <wt:tabcontent>
        <wt:form vm="@Model" width="800">
          <wt:ueditor id="u1" field="Entity.Remark" />
          <wt:row align="AlignEnum.Right">
            <wt:submitbutton disabled="true" />
            <wt:closebutton disabled="true" />
          </wt:row>
        </wt:form>
      </wt:tabcontent>
      <wt:tabcontent>
        <wt:code>
          &ltwt:form vm="@@Model" width="600"&gt
          &ltwt:ueditor field="Entity.Remark"  /&gt
          &ltwt:row align="AlignEnum.Right"&gt
          &ltwt:submitbutton disabled="true" /&gt
          &ltwt:closebutton disabled="true" /&gt
          &lt/wt:row&gt
          &lt/wt:form&gt
        </wt:code>
      </wt:tabcontent>
    </wt:tabcontents>
  </wt:tab>
  <wt:quote>
    The back-end of the document project is not connected to a real database. The uploaded pictures in the above columns will report errors.
    But no errors will be reported when actually using the framework. The interface of the framework can realize the uploading and browsing of pictures * note that the framework will automatically filter ＜ > Special characters.
    However rich text usually needs this kind of character. You can add [StringNeedLTGT] mark on the submitted back-end method to tell the framework not to filter special characters. But in this way, if someone enters JavaScript maliciously, you can't stop it. You should check and filter the content in the controller.
  </wt:quote>
  <wt:quote>
    For ApiController，[StringNeedLTGT] does not work, because it use json to deserilize parameters. If you need to have < >，you can add [JsonConverter(typeof(StringNeedLTGTConvert))] on top of the property of your model
  </wt:quote>

</wt:fieldset>

<script>
  layui.use('code', function () { layui.code({ about: false }) })
  layui.table.init('parse-table-demo', {
    limit: 100, page: false
  });
</script>
<script>
  $("#@Model.ViewDivId").parent().css("height", "auto");
</script>
